    tags: ["NAIFA", "Medicare/Medicare Advantage"],
    startDate: "2026-01-01",
    endDate: "2026-12-31",
    allDay: true,
    location: "NAIFA",
    status: "completed",
    description: "Framing: In their annual Retiree Health Cost Index, Milliman has suggested that retirees with Medigap could soon get some relief from rising healthcare costs. According to their 2025 study, the lifetime cost of out-of-pocket expenses and Medigap and Part D premiums for a couple that retires at age 65 could be $388,000, down 1.4% from 2024. Other product solutions, however, show a small increase. While Milliman emphasizes their projections are not certain, these estimations are a good enough reason for agents to explore Medigap and Part D with clients to see if it could reduce their estimated healthcare costs. • SME: Stephanie Kirk",
    link: "https://lhc.naifa.org/mcblog/why-smart-agents-are-reassessing-medigap-and-part-d-coverage",
